## `src/modules/<module>/` — Feature Module Layer

### Directory Structure

```
src/modules/<module>/
├── index.ts          # public API: export hooks, layouts, pages, types only
├── components/
│   ├── index.ts      # barrel (internal use only — NOT re-exported by root)
│   └── ...
├── constants/
│   └── index.ts
├── hooks/
│   ├── index.ts
│   └── use-<name>.ts
├── layouts/
│   └── index.tsx
├── pages/
│   ├── index.ts
│   └── <name>.page.tsx
├── types/
│   ├── index.ts
│   └── <name>.ts
└── utils/
    └── index.ts
```

### Root `index.ts` — Public API
Only export what consumers need. Components are internal.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
export * from "./hooks";
export * from "./layouts";
export * from "./pages";
export * from "./types";

// ❌ BAD — don't expose internal components
// export * from "./components";
```

### File & Component Naming

| Item | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Component files | `kebab-case.tsx` | `order-history.tsx` |
| Page files | `kebab-case.page.tsx` | `order-history.page.tsx` |
| Hook files | `use-kebab-case.ts` | `use-order-history.ts` |
| Component names | `PascalCase` | `OrderHistory` |
| Page component names | `PascalCase` + `Page` suffix | `OrderHistoryPage` |

### Hooks (`hooks/use-<name>.ts`)
- Always start with `"use client"`.
- Co-locate Zod schema + inferred type + hook logic in one file.
- Infer form types from schema: `type XFormData = z.infer<typeof xSchema>`.
- Return pre-wrapped `onSubmit` (caller doesn't call `handleSubmit` themselves).
- Export `ReturnType<typeof useX>` so form components can use it as prop type.

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
"use client";

export const orderSchema = z.object({ ... });
export type OrderFormData = z.infer<typeof orderSchema>;

export const useOrderForm = () => {
  const methods = useForm<OrderFormData>({ resolver: zodResolver(orderSchema) });
  const onSubmit = methods.handleSubmit(async (_data) => { ... });
  return { methods, onSubmit, isSubmitting: methods.formState.isSubmitting };
};
export type UseOrderFormReturn = ReturnType<typeof useOrderForm>;
```

### Pages (`pages/<name>.page.tsx`)
- Keep thin — delegate logic to components/hooks.
- Use `"use client"` (or inherit from layout).
- Handle loading + unauthenticated states at the page level.

### Components
- Set `displayName` on complex components.
- Use `@phosphor-icons/react` for all icons.
- Responsive: `useSmaller` / `useGreater` from `@/shared` for breakpoint checks.
- Tailwind spacing: use brand tokens (`p-4xl`, `gap-2xl`) — no raw pixel values.

### Shared Components — Always Prefer Over Native Elements

Always use pre-built components from `@/shared/components` instead of raw HTML elements. Never reach for a native tag when a shared component exists.

| Need | Use | Never use |
|---|---|---|
| Text / headings | `<Typography variant="..." />` | `<p>`, `<h1>`–`<h6>`, `<span>` (unstyled) |
| Clickable actions | `<Button variant="..." size="..." />` | `<button>` |
| Modal/overlay | `<Dialog>` + `<DialogContent>` + `<DialogTitle>` | Custom modal components |
| Text input | `<Input />` | `<input>` |
| Multiline input | `<Textarea />` | `<textarea>` |
| Checkbox | `<Checkbox />` | `<input type="checkbox">` |
| Dropdown | `<Select />` | `<select>` |
| Tooltip | `<Tooltip />` | Custom tooltip implementations |
| Popover | `<Popover />` | Custom popover implementations |
| Badge | `<Badge />` | Custom badge spans |
| Skeleton loader | `<Skeleton />` | Custom shimmer divs |
| Tabs | `<Tabs />` | Custom tab implementations |
| Separator | `<Separator />` | `<hr>` |
| Slide-over panel | `<Sheet />` | Custom slide-over implementations |
| Confirmation prompt | `<ConfirmationDialog />` | Custom confirm dialogs |

**Typography variants**: `display-xlarge`, `display-large`, `heading-lg`, `heading-md`, `heading-sm`, `body-xl`, `body-lg`, `body-md`, `body-sm`, `body-xs`

**Button variants**: `primary`, `secondary`, `gray`, `outlined-primary`, `outlined-secondary`, `outlined-gray`, `text-primary`, `text-secondary`, `text-gray`

**Button sizes**: `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Typography } from "@/shared/components/typography";
import { Button } from "@/shared/components/button";
import { Dialog, DialogContent, DialogTitle, DialogTrigger } from "@/shared/components/dialog";

<Typography variant="heading-md">Order Summary</Typography>
<Typography variant="body-sm" color="secondary">Select your photos below</Typography>
<Button variant="primary" size="md">Confirm Order</Button>
<Button variant="outlined-secondary" size="sm" startIcon={PencilIcon}>Edit</Button>

<Dialog>
  <DialogTrigger>Open</DialogTrigger>
  <DialogContent>
    <DialogTitle>Confirm Delete</DialogTitle>
    ...
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>

// ❌ BAD
<h3 className="text-lg font-semibold">Order Summary</h3>
<p className="text-sm text-gray-500">Select your photos below</p>
<button className="bg-black text-white px-4 py-2">Confirm Order</button>
```

> When in doubt, check `src/shared/components/index.ts` for the full list of available components before creating anything new.

### Forms
Always follow this pattern:

```
Zod schema → z.infer type → useForm + zodResolver → FormProvider → RHFInput / RHFPassword / RHFCheckbox
```

### Barrel exports
Every folder must have an `index.ts` using `export *`.

```ts
// hooks/index.ts
export * from "./use-order-form";
export * from "./use-order-history";
```

### Mutations & Queries
- All API mutations/queries live in `@/shared` (e.g., `useLoginMutation`, `useQueryMe`).
- Hooks in `src/modules/<module>/hooks/` consume them — never call `fetch` directly.
- Mock data goes in `constants/index.ts` until real API is wired.
